headline.main: EUROPEAN EXTRACTS.; Deplorable Condition of Emigrant Ships between England and the United States. Necessity and Means of Reform. From the London Times.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Commissioners of Emigration promptly deny the truth of a report which has circulated considerably, and at last found its way into one of our cotemporaries, to the effect that they were in the habit of sending up newly arrived emigrants from infected ships by the Third-avenue Railroad for embarkation to Ward's Island.

docs.lead_paragraph: Organization of the New Board. The new Board of Education, chosen at the last Charter Election, held their first meeting in their Chamber, corner of Grand and Elm-streets, last evening. Nearly all the members were present.

headline.main: ONE DAY LATER FROM ASPINWALL.; Arrival of the Yankee Blade. LATER FROM JAMAICA.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Yankee Blade arrived yesterday morning from Aspinwall, with the passengers of the Uncle Sam, from San Francisco. We are indebted to the Yankee Blade's Purser S. L. VAUGHT Esq., for early memoranda and papers from California and Kingston.

BROOKLYN CITY.; MORTALITY. FALL OF A BUILDING. FIRE.

docs.lead_paragraph: MORTALITY.--The health Officer reports 86 deaths during the week ending Saturday last. Of those, there were 36 males and 50 females, Adults, 27; children, 59. There were 8 deaths by consumption, 5 by croup, 8 of levers, and 3 by small-pox.
